name: Place
title: Place
description: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

fields.name: additionalType
fields.title: Additional Type
fields.description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

fields.name: openingHoursSpecification
fields.title: Opening Hours Specification
fields.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

fields.name: aggregateRating
fields.title: Aggregate Rating
fields.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

fields.name: map
fields.title: Map
fields.description: A URL to a map of the place.

fields.name: branchCode
fields.title: Branch Code
fields.description:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.

For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

fields.name: events
fields.title: Events
fields.description: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

fields.name: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
fields.title: Special Opening Hours Specification
fields.description:
The special opening hours of a certain place.

Use this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by openingHoursSpecification or openingHours.

fields.name: geo
fields.title: Geo
fields.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

fields.name: containedIn
fields.title: Contained In
fields.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.
